name: phosphinothricin acetyltransferase
classes: Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
comment: The substrate phosphinothricin is used as a nonselective herbicide and is a potent inhibitor of EC 6.3.1.2, glutamate---ammonia ligase, a key enzyme of nitrogen metabolism in plants [2].

references.title: Characterization of phosphinothricin acetyltransferase and C-terminal enzymatically active fusion proteins.
